Access Control & Authorization
1. Permission Definition
Define granular permissions to control system actions:
Read
Add (Create)
Update
Delete
Manage Order (Ordering / Sorting)

2. Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)
Each user is assigned a role, and each role has specific permissions.
Example Roles: Admin Instructor Content Manager Student (Read-only)
Each role maps to allowed actions on modules (Course, Lesson, Content, etc.).

3. OAuth Integration
Use OAuth for secure authentication:
Supports third-party login (Google, GitHub, etc.)
Token-based access (JWT or similar)
Scoped permissions per role
